I just learned that there is more than one Valentine's Day in South Korea!&nbsp;In fact, there are many!&nbsp;

Here are a few of them:&nbsp;

Feb 14th - Red Valentine's Day. Girls give boys chocolate, and not vice versa.
March 14th - White Valentine's Day. Boys give girls chocolate! 
April 14th - &quot;Black&quot;&nbsp;Valentine's Day. Singles congregate and eat &quot;black&quot;&nbsp;noodles to symbolize the blackness of their single hearts. I&nbsp;am not making this up. 
May 14th - &quot;Roses&quot;&nbsp;Valentine's Day. Flower exchange.
June 14th - Yellow Day - Teddy bear exchange.
July 14th - Kiss Day - self-explanatory.

I&nbsp;kind of love the Korean tendency to make up a holiday about EVERYTHING. I swear to God there is a festival every weekend here. It makes life exciting!&nbsp;

